# Feature 6 — Review & Revision Flow

## Goal
Once a designer submits a copy request, the Copy Team can review it, 
approve it, or send it back with revision notes. The designer is notified 
and can revise and resubmit.

## Request Statuses
- draft → saved but not submitted
- submitted → designer submitted, waiting for Copy Team review
- in_review → Copy Team has opened the request
- approved → Copy Team approved the copy
- changes_requested → Copy Team sent it back with notes

## Designer Flow
- Designer submits a request from the request detail page
- Status changes to "submitted"
- Designer can see the status on the dashboard and request detail page
- If status is "changes_requested", designer can see the revision notes
- Designer can update the copy selections and resubmit
- Each resubmission creates a new version in version history

## Copy Team Flow
- Copy Team sees all submitted requests on their dashboard
- They can open a request and review the generated copy
- They can leave overall revision notes (text field)
- Two action buttons: "Approve" and "Request changes"
- Approve → status changes to "approved", designer notified
- Request changes → status changes to "changes_requested", 
  revision notes saved, designer notified

## Notifications
- In-app notification badge on the nav showing unread notifications
- Notification types:
  - "Your request [title] has been approved"
  - "Your request [title] needs changes: [notes]"
  - "New request [title] submitted for review" (for Copy Team)
- Notifications stored in Firestore under notifications/{userId}
- Mark as read when clicked

## Data Structure
Request document updates:
- status (updated throughout flow)
- revisionNotes (Copy Team's feedback text)
- reviewedBy (Copy Team user ID)
- reviewedAt (timestamp)

## UI
- Status badges with colors:
  - draft → #F4F5F6 with #222629 text
  - submitted → yellow (#FFEA00) with #222629 text
  - in_review → blue with white text
  - approved → green with white text
  - changes_requested → red with white text
- Revision notes shown in a highlighted box on request detail
- Notification bell icon in nav with unread count badge
- Mobile friendly
